analysis_examples:
Example of a buffer overflow bug:
```c
char buf[128];
int len = sizeof(buf);
// This is buggy because buf[len] accesses the 129th element (index 128) when buf only has 128 elements (indices 0-127)
buf[len] = '\0';
```

Example of safe code:
```c
char buf[128];
int len = sizeof(buf);
// This is safe because it only accesses elements within bounds (indices 0-127)
buf[len-1] = '\0';
```

Example of a buffer overflow bug:
```c
char array[100];
for (int i = 0; i <= 100; i++) { // Bug: loop runs from 0 to 100 (101 iterations)
  array[i] = 0; // Out of bounds when i=100
}
```

Example of safe code:
```c
char array[100];
for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++) { // Safe: loop runs from 0 to 99 (100 iterations)
  array[i] = 0;
}
```
